com.ibm.team.repository.common.query.ast
Interface IDynamicQueryModel

All Superinterfaces:
IManyQueryModel, IQueryModel, ISingleQueryModel
All Known Subinterfaces:
IDynamicItemQueryModel
public interface IDynamicQueryModel
extends ISingleQueryModel, IManyQueryModel

Defines a query model for an item or a helper. A dynamic query model can be accessed using IItemType.getQueryModel(). Note that this is only needed when the static query model for an item type is not visible, for instance because of an inverted or soft dependency on another model. Generally, static query models should be used whenever they are visible and the types/properties are known at compile time. Note also that there are no API contracts regarding dynamic APIs - model objects may change shape, queryable properties, etc.

Since:
0.5
